The Tikray package is using the MIT license. However, it may pull in additional
optional packages that are using different licenses.

For example, the optional package extra `macropipe` pulls in the `polars-st`
package, which is using LGPL-2.1 licensed code that statically links GEOS main.

Static linking of LGPL code triggers compliance obligations (source code provision,
relinking capability, license/copyright notices) regardless of optional dependency
status.

When using this package in your software, conduct a legal/packaging review to
determine compliance measures needed and add prominent user-facing documentation
disclosing the LGPL-2.1 dependency and its implications.
